snippet.textDisplay: Ok so I think you have got Both of Mary 1 and Mary Queen of scots mixed up. The Queen Mary ship was dedicated to Mary of Teck, who was the Kings consort ( or basically queen) in the early 1900’s. Mary tudor was a ruthless leader who protested that Catholics were in the wrong and protestants were superior. Queen Mary Tudor had no connections to The Queen Mary ship whatsoever. Mary Queen of Scots was a the ruler in Scotland after her father James died just after her birth (she was the only legitimate child of James) she stayed in France for most of her childhood before returning to Scotland. She was then captured by Mary Tudors sister, Elizabeth 1, where she then died via execution on the orders of Elizabeth. Hope this helps you guys in the future.x x
